description: "Machinations!" Guest-starring Batman. Lex Luthor sets out to restore his good name and he'll need the Kryptonite ring he use to possess to do it. Now, forced to believe in the justice system, Superman must get the ring back from its present protector, the Dark Knight. Note: This story is a lead-in to the "Lord of the Ring" in Superman #168 and Detective Comics #756).
name: Machinations!

description: "Deception!" Bibbo and Yango duke it out, and Lex Luthor prepares for his upcoming trial. Meanwhile, the new Superman battles for his life against a cadre of deadly villains.
name: Deception!

description: Genesis! Part 17. Guest-starring the JLA and New Gods. When Superman heads to the Source Wall he encounters an enemy from the past, the Cyborg-Superman. But is the Last Son of Krypton's new energy powers a match for this deadly foe? Story concludes in Adventures of Superman (1939-2006) #551.
name: Genesis Anew!

description: "Within Human Reach!" This issue focuses on Ashbury Armstrong's everyday life. But how everyday can your life be when you are escorted around by Scorn, a seven-foot tall blue monster?
name: A Date With Disaster!

description: Halloween issue. "The Longest Halloween!" It's Halloween in Metropolis and Lois and Clark attend a costume party dressed as none other than the Dynamic Duo, Batman and Robin (yeah, it's as funny as it sounds). But the party is cut short when a powerful new villain crashes the festivities! Story continues in Adventures of Superman (1939-2006) #553.

Luthor and the Contessa have become proud parents! And when Lex promises his bouncing baby that "someday, all this will be yours," he's referring to Metropolis! What sinister plan does Lex have in mind to guarantee that the newest Luthor will be his successor?

Superman with his new energy-based powers wearing a containment suit is out of Metropolis to deal with some military issue somewhere far away.

Lex Luthor is remembering the time as he was a kid in a foster family. Lex shows that he had a particular bond to the girl whose name, Lena.

Luthor's attending a speech in town, a story covered by the famous reporter of the Daily Planet, Lois Lane. Meanwhile, the child of the Contessa Erica Alexandra Del Portenza is about to be given birth.

Indeed, Lex Luthor has something in mind. During the speech, the speaker is suddenly shot and at the meantime, Superman, is saving the world and the awaiting child is born.

Lex Luthor pulled the strings to get the revenge of the murder of the only girl he'd ever loved, Lena by setting up her murderer, their foster father, Casey Griggs. He was paid for killing the speaker and as Superman is not in Metropolis, the crime could not have been prevented.

After dealing with the case, Luthor came to see Doctor Cordova and take his child in his arms, Lena Luthor. After Lena's birth, Lex takes advantage of Contessa Erica's wish to be unconscious at child birth by keeping her permanently drugged and unconscious at his corporate headquarters, not wishing to share his daughter's love with anyone else.

"Double Play!" Part 1 of 3. Guest-starring the JLA. As if Superman's new powers and new look weren't jarring enough, now there are two of them. Get ready for the adventures of Superman-Blue and Superman-Red! Story continues in Adventures of Superman (1939-2006) #555.
name: Double Play

description: Superman had decided to take a more active role in saving the world from itself (see Superman (1987 - ) #142), and even went to the point to unleash an army of robotic dopplegangers to be places where he could not. Has the Man of Steel gone too far? Or is there something far more sinister at work here? Story continues in Adventures of Superman (1939-2006) #567.
name: Up In Smoke

description: "Public Hearing!" We've seen the Man of Steel read and often answer letters before (see Superman (1987- ) #64 and 109) but how does he handle hate mail? Find out in this decidedly different adventure of Superman.
name: Public Hearing

description: "Rough Day at the Office!" The Toyman, an oft silly opponent, had suddenly turned darker and became far more dangerous to others an himself (see Superman (1987- ) #84-85 where he murdered Cat Grant's son). The Last Son of Krypton attempts one of his most difficult challenges. Can the Toyman be rehabilitated?
name: Rough Day at the Office

description: The One Man JLA! Part 1 of 4. "Secret Origins: The Knight!" Ever wonder what the DC Universe would be like if Krypton hadn't exploded? Maybe Kal-el would have become the greatest Green Lantern of all time? Find out in this Elseworlds-style epic where a super-villain attempts to find out what makes the Man of Steel a Superman. Story continues in Adventures of Superman (1939-2006) #570.
name: Secret Origins, Part 1: The Knight

description: "Champions!" Superman has his hands full on a far off world with tree super-powered aliens. Plus, when Lois finds out the name of Lana Lang's baby, Clark may have some explaining to do.
name: Duel on a Distant World!

description: "Strange Visitor!" Part 1 of 4. Who is this strange woman who possess powers like Superman's - powers like when he was electric-blue Superman that is? And what is her connection to someone very close to the Man of Steel? Story continues in Adventures of Superman (1939-2006) #572.
name: The Arrival of...Strange Visitor !

description: Last issue for Jurgens - Special Extra-Sized 150th issue - White background cover. "Earth's Final Hour!" With a title like "Earth's Final Hour" it can only mean one thing - Brainiac is back and he's deadlier than ever! And as if that weren't bad enough, Vartox, Vestion, and Paz (1st seen in Superman (1987- ) #148) arrive on Earth and they aren't on the side of angels.

The Daily Planet returns as a new era for the Man of Steel begins! "Faster than a speeding bullet," SUPERMAN FOR ALL SEASONS writer Jeph Loeb joins artists Mike McKone and Marlo Alquiza for a back-to-basics issue that reveals the shocking reason Lex Luthor has given the Planet back to Perry White. Plus, what villain's son is heading to Earth for a collision with the Man of Steel?
name: We're Back!

description:
Aquaman makes a cameo in an exciting issue, featuring a striking cover by Dwayne Turner (Curse of the Spawn) and Danny Miki, who provide all of this month's Superman-ongoing titles' covers!

All his life Superman has kept himself in check, never unleashing his full power for fear of killing someone. Now the son of Mongul is asking him to unleash his full potential in order to save Earth, but in doing so will the Man of Steel lose himself? Plus, Jimmy shoots the scoop of the century, which has everyone asking, "Who is Mrs. Superman?"

"1999 1"--Triangle in upper left hand corner.
name: The Fury of Superman!; Deadline U.S.A.

description:
Done with his lethal training at the side of young Mongul, Superman and the junior villain head into the depths of space to confront Imperiex. This enigmatic being is powerful enough to live in a black hole and all too ready to turn the Earth into one! Will Superman's new battle skills be enough to stop Imperiex? And can the Man of Steel trust his new ally?

Imperex appearing for the first time.

JLA guest star. The Man of Steel is faced with a pair of dilemmas. One of which is finding gifts for the JLA for the holidays. The other problem is simply making him nuts! Meanwhile, in outer space, the time cops known as the Linear Men are beaten by a terrible force. One that's headed towards Earth...and Superman!
name: What Do You Get the JLA for Christmas?

description:
Overview

It's the startling, true origin of the Last Son of Krypton. That's right -- readers only think they know the truth about Superman, but this month the lie is finally revealed and the Man of Steel's real heritage is uncovered. This issue features a special holographic foil background enhancement on the cover (of an exploding Krypton) at no extra cost.
name: The Real Truth About Krypton !

description:
Overview

Part 1 of "Return to Krypton," the storyline running through all the Superman books in February. Taking Lois with him, Superman returns to the land of his birth - but now it's seen in a way it hasn't looked in almost twenty years. Can Superman save this Silver Age Krypton from its destruction?
name: Return to Krypton Part 1: The World of Kryptonopolis !

description: The Kents and Lanes have a rousing dinner together; Perry reveals that Bruce Wayne has been the secret backer for the Daily Planet; Lois and Bats begin their attempt to steal the Kryptonite Ring from President Luthor.
name: This Looks Like a Job For...Batman & Lois !

description: "Infestation," the 4-part storyline that runs through all the Superman books in April, begins here! The alien Korsa Majalis journeys to Earth to enlist Superman's aid, after Korsa's planet is corrupted and turned into energy by the sentient space virus Viroxx. But is Superman enough to halt the course of this seemingly unstoppable cosmic disease?
name: Infestation, Part 1 of 4

description:
Clark Kent and Lois Lane have taken Krypto for a stroll to the park. Then Superman's old enemy Mongul comes down. Krypto attacks at once, with Superman joining in, shortly afterwards. But more surprise awaits Superman.

Mongul has brought with him his sister, Mongal. Together they give Superman a tough fight. But Superman is able to shake off both of them. Mongal escapes, leaving Mongul behind to be taken into custody.
Superman thinks it will be safe to leave Krypto at the Fortress of Solitude and acts likewise.
name: Bad Dog!

description: " Part 1 The vanished planet Pluto reemerges and Superman must investigate, but he soon finds himself battling a deadly time-displaced Fatal Five. Meanwhile, President Luthor has a close encounter with an alien woman who brings portents of destruction. Will the President listen or will it be a day that will live in infamy?
name: Of Course, You Know, This Means...Warworld!

description: " Part 12. Superman is at ground zero witnessing the aftermath of Imperiex's first strike. He goes toe to toe with one of Imperiex's destroyer probes ? but stopping it comes at a price...and this is only the beginning! For more information, see the feature article.
name: Death Be Not Proud

description: " Part 25. With all the death around him Superman has no choice but to deliver himself into the hands of Lex Luthor and become part of the "Metropolis Project," as the Man of Steel and Strange Visitor form a new, living weapon. Will Imperiex finally fall to the sacrifice made by the heroes? For more information, see the feature article.
name: The Red Badge of Courage

description: Superman and his allies return to Tribunal World and debate Superman's and Mope's sentences one last time; Both Superman and Tribunal Prime receive their final punishments, and Superman returns to Earth and Lois.
name: Justice!

description: Lori Lemaris returns, and Lois isn't happy.
name: Lori Lemaris Returns!

description: Its a race against time as Superman and Impulse are trying to locate several bombs hidden around the world and will go off if not found. With each one found, a new clue to the location of the next bomb is revealed.
name: Scavenger Hunt

description: Lord Satanus returns as the DMN drug problem intensifies, leaving Metropolis at the mercy of rampaging drug-addicted monsters!; Other than that, everyone in the city is experiencing more than their share of good luck these days--all but Clark and Lois. Jerry Siegel 1914-1996 biography/tribute.
name: Monster Mash!

description: Clark pays his folks a visit in Smallville, but he's just not having any luck at all, especially when a tornado threatens to destroy the Kents' rebuilt home and the rest of Smallville! Comics Buyer's Guide 1996 Fan Awards article.
name: Toasted!

description: Brainiac takes control of Lovelace Psychiatric Hospital and tries to effect a mind-swap with a certain man of steel in "Identity Crisis Chapter One: Cages." Continued in Action Comics (1938 DC) #723.
name: Identity Crisis, Part 1: Cages

description: Parasite breaks into S.T.A.R. Labs, freeing all the creatures being held in the lower levels; Story continues in Action Comics #724.
name: Freak Show!

description: Dana's infatuation with Superman gets serious when she develops super-powers and goes ballastic after Big Blue spurs her; After all, it's not just a crush. With her, you could call it...OBSESSION!
name: Deadly Obsession!

description: Misa invades Project Cadmus and attacks Floyd Barstow when he confronts her, Clark Kent is kept hopping at the Daily Planet filling in for Perry White, Floyd Barstow turns into Anomaly when coming in contact with blood at the Hotel Royer, Superman defeats Anomaly by turning him to energy and Floyd Barstow wakes up back at his hotel wondering what is happening to him; Continued from Superman #116; Continued in Action Comics #726.
name: Doppelgangster

description: WGBS goes live with Jimmy Olsen's big announcement regarding Superman's secret identity. The Guardian is busy fighting for his life against Boss Moxie, Dabney Donovan and their group of kooky clones.
name: The Secret

description: GENESIS continues to complicate Superman's new powers! Superman's containment suit is lined with printed circuitry, which is necessary to keep the Man Beyond Tomorrow intact as a being of solid energy. But the circuitry that's saving him makes him the prime target of a little intergalactic piggyback ride for the Cyborg! Look out, Earth, here he comes!
name: Genesis For Humanity

description: People are mysteriously disappearing from Metropolis! They walk down a gray city street and they vanish, leaving behind tearful families! Does this have anything to do with the Parasite? Well, no, but he's what's occupying Superman's attention at the moment.
name: Power Grab!

description:
Metropolis has been plagued by a series of mysterious disappearances. Citizens are vanishing beneath the streets of the city. Something is out therebut who can go after it? Not Superman-he has his hands full with three remarkable new villains! Plus, Scorn and Ashbury meet Misa of the Revenge Squad!

Superman vs the Millennium Guard: Hunab, Dagda and Amun. Superman is out gunned and only has his old pal Jimmy Olsen to help in his time of need. Can Jimmy do what Superman cannot?

"1997 49"--Triangle in upper left hand corner.

Storyline continues on: Action Comics #740 - A Bag, A Bone, & A Hank of Hair
name: Energy Crisis

description: Superman finally confronts the strange creature responsible for the mysterious disappearances that have been plaguing the city of Metropolis. Plus, the Man Beyond Tomorrow is introduced to Luthor's baby!
name: It Lurks Beneath Metropolis!

description: The strange story of Superman Red and Superman Blue continues in a barroom brawl it takes two Men of Energy to stop! Plus, Jimmy drags Ashbury and Scorn into a pitched battle with his old nemeses-the cult called Black Crucible!
name: Superman Red vs. Superman Blue

description: Twice as many thrills! Twice as many exploits! Because there's twice as many Supermen! This issue features two big stories of the Last Sons of Krypton. Superman Red stares down the harbingers of doom known as the Millennium Guard in "Three to One," while Superman Blue defends Jimmy Olsen and Misa in "I Was Alone Against GargoxA Really Big Monster!"

A fight like this only happens once in a thousand years as the Giants reach the nation of Markovia! Local heroes Geo-Force and Terra do what they can against the behemoths, with help from guest stars Steel, Supergirl, the Teen Titans, Flash and Green Lantern! Meanwhile, Superman Blue, J'onn J'onzz and Aquaman team up to keep a giant from crushing Lori Lemaris' underwater city.
name: Behold! The Millennium Giants!

description:
After a unique baseball game between the members of the Superman family, Jimmy is apparently turned into an alien who turns objects into gold; Luthor captures the alien to take advantage of his transmuting abilities; Supes heads up a rescue; and the alien turns out to be a real E.T. wearing Jimmy's clothes.

Notes:

  • "Watch This Space" "Number 98-7" one page memorial text piece on the life of Archie Goodwin. Plus, "Read This Space" featuring comics books that were to be released for the week.
  • Triangle 1998 #22.
  • Chronological continuation from Superman Forever #1.
  • Chronological continuation in Action Comics #745.
name: Another Typical Day

description:
Superman blows up a comet brought down by Brainiac, giving everyone in Metropolis superpowers! Everyone except for Dan Turpin, who never wanted superpowers to begin with. Could it all be a gag by an imp from the Fifth Dimension?

Notes:

  • "Watch This Space" "Number 98-12" one page text piece featuring the Riddler's Revenge roller coaster opening at Six Flags Magic Mountain. DC personnel head to Coney Island for the day. A continuing tribute to Archie Goodwin. At SUNY-Stony Brook held their 17th annual sci-fi and comic book convention I-Con. Plus, Grant Morrison aiding in the upcoming One Million storyline event. Finally, "Read This Space!" featuring comics books that were to be released for the week.
  • Triangle 1998 #26.
  • Chronological continuation from Superman #136.
  • Chronological continuation in Action Comics #746.
name: The Day of the Super-Comet

description: The JLA guest-stars in "Superman's Strangest Adventure" Part 2 of an unreal 4-part story! The League continues to search for Superman, unaware that the Man of Steel believes himself to be on the planet Rann, where he believes himself to be the omniscient, omnipresent Overseer of the entire world! But what does Rann's greatest hero, Adam Strange, think about this newcomer to the neighborhood?
name: Secret Origins, Part 2: The Invader From Earth!

description: What happens when the villainous Atomic Skull learns that there's a movie taking liberties with his life ? and it's being filmed on the streets of Metropolis? Will on-set sabotage be just the beginning? Can Superman get the explosive situation under control before all Metropolis pays the price?
name: It Came From Hollywood!

description: Superman battles side by side a mysterious new super-heroine in part two of the four-part story "Strange Visitor!" Wearing the Man of Steel's "electric blue" costume, Strange Visitor has won our hero's trust by saving a woman's life. Now the heroic duo faces a threat from that woman's husband, a super-powered gangster who imagines himself to be the new god of war!
name: Who Is Strange Visitor? Chapter Two; When?

description: The new era continues with a look at Superman through the eyes of ordinary people! Flashbacks to Smallville and young Clark Kent's first attempt to "leap tall buildings" contrast with a modern adventure where Clark, not Superman, must come to the aid of a lone man making a stand against Luthor. Plus, a brief appearance by Luthor's new bodyguards -- Mercy (based on the character from The New Batman/Superman Adventures) and her partner, Hope.
name: Higher Ground

description:
A stranger is giving DMN, a derivative of the dreaded Demon Drug, to some kids in Suicide Slums.

The next day, Superman is going toe to toe with the super-villain, Gabriel Van Daniken, when suddenly Obsession returns to the scene. Her new costume make people mistake her for Mrs. Superman. Superman tries to drive her away but she does not listen and beats him up.

The kids who had taken DMN the other night have turned into demons and are attacking innocent people. Superman begs Obsession to release him and let him fight the monsters. Obsession insists in accompanying him to the crime scene.

They take down the demons together and are having a chat when suddenly a demons attempts to attack from behind. Obsession pushes Superman away and takes the full brunt of the demon's power. Then she declares her love for Superman and dies in his hands. Superman is heart-broken and resolves not to comment about the incident.
name: Something Borrow, Something Blue

description: Will Luthor die before the fat lady sings? It's a night at the opera for Mr. and Mrs. Clark Kent, but our hero's superheroic duties may ruin the evening for the couple. That is if an assasination attempt on Lex Luthor's life doesn't first!
name: La MORT du LUTHOR!

description: Continuing the Brainiac 13 storyline. New Metropolis has risen, but has a new Superman as well? Or is it one we've seen before? The battle heats up as Luthor, Mercy and Hope fight alongside the old Brainiac in hopes of finding Brainiac 13's weakness while the world teeters on the brink of doom!
name: Y2K, Part 3 of 5: A Hero & A City Reborn!

description: Smallville stories continue as Superman deals with the xenophobia of his own home town, where even the Man of Steel isn't trusted. Meanwhile, Luthor ? accompanied by Mercy ? surveys his new Metropolis; and Lois and Clark seem to suffer some marital problems.
name: A Tale of Two Cities

description: New series writer J.M. DeMatteis makes his debut as Superman and Lois travel to an alien utopia in hopes of helping their troubled relationship. But there's a terror in paradise, and death to the couple is its counselling! Plus, Superman shows signs of being...sick?
name: Double Trouble in Paradise!

description: Lois has vanished! But before Superman can even begin to search for her, the new, improved Prankster strikes! This is no laughing matter, especially with Superman's health beginning to fail! Plus, another new foe ? the Adversary ? arrives on the scene, hoping to make a name for himself by defeating the Man of Steel.
name: Pranked!

description: ECLIPSO: THE DARKNESS WITHIN Annuals Crossover Event continues. A last-ditch effort to reclaim Superman from Eclipso's control is made as those heroes remaining uneclipsed, including Lobo and Guy Gardner, band together to select one among them for a suicide mission to the sun in order to bring back some raw sunlight to 'cure' Superman.
name: In Blackest Night

description: The BLOODLINES Summer Annual crossover event continues from Justice League America Annual #7. The teenage Superman is electrified when Sparx - the latest infusion of New Blood in the DC Universe - makes her shocking debut in Metropolis! And, as the super-powered New Blood sprout up across the DC Universe, a strange family of meta-humans sacrifices its only non-powered child to the hideous extraterrestrial parasites! BLOODLINES continues in Hawkman Annual #1.
name: Blood Relations!

description:
In a strange ulternate universe, The Hordeattacksearth and wins. The heroes of earth have either been killed or gone missing. Years later there is talk of an attack on the horde. Hearing this Jimmy Olsen goes on a search for the heroes that are left from the forgotten age. Will Jimmy so called heroes have the Hope and Will to take on the Horde, or will there distress and lost get in the way of mankinds last hope?

Continues in Superboy Annual #1
name: The Super Seven Part I: The Longest Night

description:
The story flashes back to ten years ago when Superman first arrived in Metropolis. He ended a standoff between terrorists and a S.W.A.T. team, rescued children from a fire, apprehended bank robbers, prevented a subway disaster, and foiled an armored car heist. But despite all that opinions on Superman were sharply divided. Some, like S.W.A.T. Captain Reagan, claim that he is a menace who would never be given a badge, yet routinely takes the law into his own hands. While others like Sergeant Dan Turpin see him as a great asset in the war on crime. And still others like Officer Maggie Sawyer and Detective Henderson are unsure how the police should proceed.

While the general public is still in awe of this newcomer, and reporters like Lois Lane are scrambling to get the first interview with him, the reaction from Metropolis' criminal underworld is quite different. Called together by Ugly Manheim, son of crime lord Boss Moxie, they unite under the banner Intergang.

Intergang takes over a luxury hotel, and the police and S.W.A.T. teams show up only to learn that Intergang has Maggie Sawyer hostage, is armed with technology the likes of which they've never seen, and a super powered ally of their own, the alien Kalibak! Can even Superman save them?
name: Year One: Truth and Justice
Terror of the Sierra Madre; The Return of Saganowahna The Journey of the Horseman

description: Blasted a year into the future, Superman stands as the final line of defense for Earth. And the threat he's trying to protect the planet from? Himself!
name: Family Reunion: Part Two

description: Ben, a mild-mannered staffer with a huge crush on Lois, accidentally becomes the object of the reporter's affections when she's hit by a super villain's hypnotic device.
name: Sullivan's Girl Friend, Lois Lane

description: Superman's greatest enemies have never figured out that Clark Kent and the Man of Steel are the same person--until now! Who's learned the world's greatest secret, and how can Clark prove him wrong before he exposes it to the world?
name: Clark Kent Is Superman - And I Can Prove It!

description: The Man of Steel's been possessed, and only one man can save him...or at least stop him! An ancient evil is on the loose in Metropolis, and it's taken control of Superman! It's a job only the sorcerous Dr. Fate can handle. At least we hope so, or he may have to banish the Man of Steel to a place with extremely warm temperatures!
name: Sanctuary

description: The Toyman's toys are pulling off a rash of crimes throughout Metropolis, but the Toyman insists he isn't behind it. Now Superman must find out if there's another mastermind at work, or if the Toyman's just playing games to hatch a bigger, deadlier scheme!
name: Never Play With the Toyman's Toys!

description: This whole issue looks like a job for Superman, bank robberies, plane hijackings, people trapped in mine shafts, and oh yeah, a kid's missing dog. Can even the Man of Steel cover all these bases, or will he have to choose one emergency over the other?
name: This Is a Job For Superman

description: For a change of pace, Mr. Mxyzptlk tries to do Superman a good turn to make up for past animosity. But the "favor" he does for the Man of Steel makes our hero angrier than we've ever seen him!
name: Old Wounds

description: Twenty-two single-page stories in a single issue! Featuring art by an array of artists that includes Ty Templeton, Rick Burchett, Philip Bond, Joe Staton, Craig Rousseau, Aluir Amancio, Neil Vokes, Bret Blevins, Cameron Stewart, Mike Manley, Darwyn Cooke, and more, the stories focus on the Man of Steel, his supporting cast and several of his deadliest enemies, including Luthor, Metallo and Mr. Mxyzptlk!
name: 22 Stories in a Single Bound

description: A street thug finds a Mother Box!
name: Are You My Mother Box?

description: The Commander, the manipulative malefactor with the power to force anyone to obey his orders, returns! And his only desire is to have all of Metropolis kill one man: Superman! How can the Man of Steel fight an entire city that has turned against him?
name: Law and Orders

description: In "Poker Face," the galactic bounty hunter Lobo loses in a poker game, but his bet was the planet Earth! Now the alien winner has taken claim and control of the world, leaving it up to Superman to save the day once again. But the alien isn't about to give up his prize that easily...
name: Poker Face

description: In "Four-Point Perspective," four eyewitnesses recount a battle between Superman and Kalibak of Apokolips, and how their lives have been affected by what they've seen.
name: 4 Point Perspective

description: Superstar artist Alex Ross (KINGDOM COME) supplies the painted cover for this issue! In "What Lurks Below," a mall opening in Metropolis uncovers an arcane entity that has existed in the city for a thousand years! But when this entity becomes a threat to the city, will the Man of Steel be able to stop it in time?
name: What Lurks Below

description: In "Ghost Flowers," a mysterious presence stalks a young woman through the streets of Metropolis. But when the Man of Steel tries to protect the woman, he can't! The presence is mystical in nature...and Superman is powerless against magic!
name: Ghost Flowers

description: In this issue Lois Lane is investigating rumors of a laboratory that is performing cruel experiments on apes by a scientist named Dr. Thomas Meyers. Unfortunately her and Clark Kent arrive a little too late as one of the test subjects, an ape named Titano is affected by radiation and grows to King Kong proportions.
name: Tears For Titano!

description:
"The Cadmus Project" - A top secret research facility loses a group of 'Alpha Subjects', a group that looks suspiciously like the Newsboy Legion mysteriously appears in Metropolis, and a superhero that looks a lot like the World War II hero The Guardian challenges Superman. What do all these things have in common? The Man of Steel intends to find out!

"Love's Labors... "Private Lives" - When Barrage puts Dan Turpin in the hospital, he begins to reevaluate things, including his relationship with Captain Sawyer.

Notes:

  • "The Cadmus Project" written by Roger Stern, penciled by Ron Frenz, inked by Brett Breeding, lettered by John Costanza and colored by Petra Scotese.
  • "Love's Labors... "Private Lives" written, penciled and inked by John Byrne, lettered by Bill Oakley and colored by Shelley Eiber.
name: The Cadmus Project / Love's Labors... "Private Lives"

description:
Waverider looks into a possible future of Superman. He sees that Clark and Lois get married, but Lois is blown up in a nuclear explosion caused by Intergang. This makes Superman go on a rampage removing the world's nuclear arsenal and becoming the world's police.

After he accidentally kills seven men aboard a nuclear submarine, the president asks Batman to "take care" of Superman.

Notes:

  • Brainiac and Bruno Mannheim cameo appearances.
  • James Gordon is the mayor of Gotham City in the future.
  • Herbert Forrest is the president of the United States in the future.
  • Chronological continuation from Armageddon 2001 #1.
  • Chronological continuation in Batman Annual #15.
name: Execution 2001

first_appearance_locations.name: Stryker's Island Maximum Security Internment Center

location_credits.name: Stryker's Island Maximum Security Internment Center

description: ECLIPSO: THE DARKNESS WITHIN Annual Crossover Event continues. Lois Lane becomes 'eclipsed' by the evil of Eclipso, while Superman confronts an entire village of Eclipsos.
name: Enduring the Night

description: The BLOODLINES Summer Annual crossover continues from New Teen Titans (1984) Annual #9. So greedy are the alien parasites Gemir and Venev that they stoop to attacking even dead humans, one of whom is a woman recently killed by Lex Luthor II. Myriad, this Annual's New Blood infusion into the DC Universe, joins with the new Superman (Cyborg Superman) in an effort to learn more about each of their forgotten pasts. BLOODLINES continues in Green Lantern (1990 2nd Series) Annual #2.
name: Myriad!

description:
Chapter Titles

  • Chapter One: Tiger, Tiger
  • Chapter Two: Lord of the Wolves
  • Chapter Three: Civilization!
  • Chapter Four: Perdition's Flame

The Elseworlds Annuals, the DC Universe's journey into remote realms of possibility, continue. In the jungles of 19th century India, a "man-cub" from the sky is raised by wolves to become the most ferocious and powerful predator the world has ever seen. It's K'l'l of the Jungle, and it's Captain Sir Richard Francis Burton's task to tame the super-powered, feral wild man...if he can!
name: The Feral Man of Steel
